  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study will assess how the current VHV (VHV=CHW, community health worker) scope can be
      expanded to include iCCM and if such group interventions can provide improved access to
      treatment for children.

      In rural SW Uganda, can iCCM provided by lay volunteers, increase the proportion of children
      with diarrhoea receiving ORS/Zn, ARI receiving anti-biotics, and fever/malaria receiving
      anti-malarials?
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
